SIMPLE: excuss
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Excuss
<hw>Ex*cuss"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>excussus</ets>. p. p. of <ets>excutere</ets> to shake off;
<ets>ex</ets> out, from + <ets>quatere</ets> to shake. Cf.
<er>Quash</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To shake off; to discard.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To <qex>excuss</qex> the notation of a Geity out of their
minds.</q> <rj><qau>Bp. Stillingfleet.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To inspect; to investigate; to decipher.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To take some pains in excusing some old monuments.</q> <rj><qau>F.
Junius (1654).</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To seize and detain by law, as goods.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Ayliffe.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Excussion</ent>⟦br⟧
